    "Let x:= (x 0, x 1,..., x p-1) denote a row of tabular data X ∈ R N ×p after applying the YJT and standardization.",
    "Let y:= DFT(x) = (y 0, y 1,..., y p-1) be its frequency-domain representation obtained by the DFT.",
    "Since the DFT satisfies conjugate symmetry, i.e., y t = y p-t for any t, it suffices Algorithm 1 Watermark embedding of TAB-DRW 1: Input: Tabular data X ∈ R N ×p, parameters γ ∈ [0, 1] and δ ∈ [-1, 1].",
    "2: Initial: Transform X using YJT and standardization (still denoted as X for simplicity).",
    "3: for each row x in X do 4:Compute y ← DFT(x) and generate pseudorandom bits {ζ t } m t=1 via Algorithm 3."
